96     /**
97      * Common code to translate CAst to IR. Must be specialized by each language to
98      * handle semantics appropriately.
99      */
100     public abstract class AstTranslator extends CAstVisitor<AstTranslator.WalkContext> implements ArrayOpHandler, TranslatorToIR {

103        * does the language care about using type-appropriate default values? For
104        * Java, the answer is yes (ints should get a default value of 0, null for
105        * pointers, etc.). For JavaScript, the answer is no, as any variable can hold
106        * the value 'undefined'.
107        */

214       protected boolean isExceptionLabel(Object label) {
215         if (label == null)
216           return false;
217         if (label instanceof Boolean)
218           return false;
219         if (label instanceof Number)
220           return false;
221         if (label == CAstControlFlowMap.SWITCH_DEFAULT)
222           return false;
223         return true;
224       }

254       /**
255        * generate prologue code for each function body
256        */
257       protected void doPrologue(WalkContext context) {
258         // perform a lexical write to copy the value stored in the local
259         // associated with each parameter to the lexical name
260         final CAstEntity entity = context.top();
261         Set<String> exposedNames = entity2ExposedNames.get(entity);
262         if (exposedNames != null) {
263           int i = 0;
264           for (String arg : entity.getArgumentNames()) {
265             if (exposedNames.contains(arg)) {
266               final Scope currentScope = context.currentScope();
267               Symbol symbol = currentScope.lookup(arg);
268               assert symbol.getDefiningScope() == currentScope;
269               int argVN = symbol.valueNumber();
270               CAstType type = (entity.getType() instanceof CAstType.Method)?
271                 (CAstType)((CAstType.Method)entity.getType()).getArgumentTypes().get(i):
272                 topType();
273               Access A = new Access(arg, context.getEntityName(entity), makeType(type), argVN);
274               context.cfg().addInstruction(new AstLexicalWrite(context.cfg().currentInstruction, A));
275             }
276           }
277         }
278       }

286       /**
287        * get the value number for a name defined locally (i.e., within the current
288        * method) by looking up the name in context.currentScope(). Note that the
289        * caller is responsible for ensuring that name is defined in the local scope.
290        */
291       protected int doLocalRead(WalkContext context, String name, TypeReference type) {
292         CAstEntity entity = context.top();
293         Set<String> exposed = entity2ExposedNames.get(entity);
294         if (exposed != null && exposed.contains(name)) {
295           return doLexReadHelper(context, name, type);
296         }
297         return context.currentScope().lookup(name).valueNumber();
298       }
299     
300       /**
301        * add an {@link AssignInstruction} to context.cfg() that copies rval to the
302        * value number of local nm. Note that the caller is responsible for ensuring
303        * that nm is defined in the local scope.
304        */
305       protected void doLocalWrite(WalkContext context, String nm, TypeReference type, int rval) {
306         CAstEntity entity = context.top();
307         Set<String> exposed = entity2ExposedNames.get(entity);
308         if (exposed != null && exposed.contains(nm)) {
309           // use a lexical write
310           doLexicallyScopedWrite(context, nm, type, rval);
311           return;
312         }
313         int lval = context.currentScope().lookup(nm).valueNumber();
314         if (lval != rval) {
315           context.cfg().addInstruction(new AssignInstruction(context.cfg().currentInstruction, lval, rval));
316         }
317       }

319       /**
320        * Note that the caller is responsible for ensuring that name is defined in a
321        * lexical scope.
322        * 
323        * @param node
324        *          the AST node representing the read
325        * @param context
326        * @param name
327        * @return
328        */
329       protected int doLexicallyScopedRead(CAstNode node, WalkContext context, final String name, TypeReference type) {
330         return doLexReadHelper(context, name, type);
331       }

334        * @param name A variable name

336        */

338         return false;

341       /**
342        * we only have this method to avoid having to pass a node parameter at other
343        * call sites, as would be required for
344        * {@link #doLexicallyScopedRead(CAstNode, WalkContext, String)}
345        */
346       private int doLexReadHelper(WalkContext context, final String name, TypeReference type) {
347         Symbol S = context.currentScope().lookup(name);
348         Scope definingScope = S.getDefiningScope();
349         CAstEntity E = definingScope.getEntity();
350         // record in declaring scope that the name is exposed to a nested scope
351         addExposedName(E, E, name, definingScope.lookup(name).valueNumber(), false, context);
352         final String entityName = context.getEntityName(E);
353         int result = context.currentScope().allocateTempValue();
354         Access A = new Access(name, entityName, type, result);
355         context.cfg().addInstruction(new AstLexicalRead(context.cfg().currentInstruction, A));
356         markExposedInEnclosingEntities(context, name, definingScope, type, E, entityName, false);
357         return result;
358       }
359     
360       /**
361        * record name as exposed for the current entity and for all enclosing
362        * entities up to that of the defining scope, since if the name is updated via
363        * a call to a nested function, SSA for these entities may need to be updated
364        * with the new definition
365        * 
366        * @param context
367        * @param name
368        * @param definingScope
369        * @param E
370        * @param entityName
371        * @param isWrite
372        */
373       private void markExposedInEnclosingEntities(WalkContext context, final String name, Scope definingScope, TypeReference type, CAstEntity E,
374           final String entityName, boolean isWrite) {
375         Scope curScope = context.currentScope();
376         while (!curScope.equals(definingScope)) {
377           final Symbol curSymbol = curScope.lookup(name);
378           final int vn = curSymbol.valueNumber();
379           final Access A = new Access(name, entityName, type, vn);
380           final CAstEntity entity = curScope.getEntity();
381           if (entity != definingScope.getEntity()) {
382             addExposedName(entity, E, name, vn, isWrite, context);
383             // record the access; later, the Accesses in the instruction
384             // defining vn will be adjusted based on this information; see
385             // patchLexicalAccesses()
386             addAccess(context, entity, A);
387           }
388           curScope = curScope.getParent();
389         }
390       }
391     
392       /**
393        * Note that the caller is responsible for ensuring that name is defined in a
394        * lexical scope.
395        * 
396        */
397       protected void doLexicallyScopedWrite(WalkContext context, String name, TypeReference type, int rval) {
398         Symbol S = context.currentScope().lookup(name);
399         Scope definingScope = S.getDefiningScope();
400         CAstEntity E = definingScope.getEntity();
401         // record in declaring scope that the name is exposed to a nested scope
402         addExposedName(E, E, name, definingScope.lookup(name).valueNumber(), true, context);
403     
404         // lexically-scoped variables must be written in their scope each time
405         Access A = new Access(name, context.getEntityName(E), type, rval);
406         context.cfg().addInstruction(new AstLexicalWrite(context.cfg().currentInstruction, A));
407         markExposedInEnclosingEntities(context, name, definingScope, type, E, context.getEntityName(E), true);
408       }

410       /**
411        * generate instructions for a read of a global
412        */
413       protected int doGlobalRead(CAstNode node, WalkContext context, String name, TypeReference type) {
414         // Global variables can be treated as lexicals defined in the CG root, or
415         if (treatGlobalsAsLexicallyScoped()) {
416     
417           int result = context.currentScope().allocateTempValue();
418           Access A = new Access(name, null, type, result);
419           context.cfg().addInstruction(new AstLexicalRead(context.cfg().currentInstruction, A));
420           addAccess(context, context.top(), A);
421           return result;
422     
423           // globals can be treated as a single static location
424         } else {
425           int result = context.currentScope().allocateTempValue();
426           FieldReference global = makeGlobalRef(name);
427           context.cfg().addInstruction(new AstGlobalRead(context.cfg().currentInstruction, result, global));
428           return result;
429         }
430       }
431     
432       /**
433        * generate instructions for a write of a global
434        */
435       protected void doGlobalWrite(WalkContext context, String name, TypeReference type, int rval) {
436     
437         // Global variables can be treated as lexicals defined in the CG root, or
438         if (treatGlobalsAsLexicallyScoped()) {
439     
440           Access A = new Access(name, null, type, rval);
441           context.cfg().addInstruction(new AstLexicalWrite(context.cfg().currentInstruction, A));
442           addAccess(context, context.top(), A);
443     
444           // globals can be treated as a single static location
445         } else {
446           FieldReference global = makeGlobalRef(name);
447           context.cfg().addInstruction(new AstGlobalWrite(context.cfg().currentInstruction, global, rval));
448         }
449       }

458       /**
459        * creates a reference to a global named globalName. the declaring type and
460        * type of the global are both the root type.
461        */
462       protected FieldReference makeGlobalRef(String globalName) {
463         TypeReference rootTypeRef = TypeReference.findOrCreate(loader.getReference(), AstTypeReference.rootTypeName);
464         return FieldReference.findOrCreate(rootTypeRef, Atom.findOrCreateUnicodeAtom("global " + globalName), rootTypeRef);
465       }

492       /**
493        * for keeping position information for the generated SSAInstructions and SSA
494        * locals
495        */
496       private static class AstDebuggingInformation implements DebuggingInformation {
497         private Position codeBodyPosition;
498     
499         private String[][] valueNumberNames;
500     
501         private Position[] instructionPositions;
502     
503         AstDebuggingInformation(Position codeBodyPosition, Position[] instructionPositions, String[] names) {
504           this.codeBodyPosition = codeBodyPosition;
505     
506           this.instructionPositions = instructionPositions;
507     
508           valueNumberNames = new String[names.length][];
509           for (int i = 0; i < names.length; i++) {
510             if (names[i] != null) {
511               valueNumberNames[i] = new String[] { names[i] };
512             } else {
513               valueNumberNames[i] = new String[0];
514             }
515           }
516         }
517     
518         @Override
519         public Position getCodeBodyPosition() {
520           return codeBodyPosition;
521         }
522     
523         @Override
524         public Position getInstructionPosition(int instructionOffset) {
525           return instructionPositions[instructionOffset];
526         }
527     
528         @Override
529         public String[][] getSourceNamesForValues() {
530           return valueNumberNames;
531         }
532       }

544       /**
545        * basic block implementation used in the CFGs constructed during the
546        * IR-generating AST traversal
547        */
548       protected final static class PreBasicBlock implements INodeWithNumber, IBasicBlock<SSAInstruction> {
549         private static final int NORMAL = 0;
550     
551         private static final int HANDLER = 1;
552     
553         private static final int ENTRY = 2;
554     
555         private static final int EXIT = 3;
556     
557         private int kind = NORMAL;
558     
559         private int number = -1;
560     
561         private int firstIndex = -1;
562     
563         private int lastIndex = -2;
564     
565         private final List<SSAInstruction> instructions = new ArrayList<SSAInstruction>();
566     
567         @Override
568         public int getNumber() {
569           return getGraphNodeId();
570         }
571     
572         @Override
573         public int getGraphNodeId() {
574           return number;
575         }
576     
577         @Override
578         public void setGraphNodeId(int number) {
579           this.number = number;
580         }
581     
582         @Override
583         public int getFirstInstructionIndex() {
584           return firstIndex;
585         }
586     
587         void setFirstIndex(int firstIndex) {
588           this.firstIndex = firstIndex;
589         }
590     
591         @Override
592         public int getLastInstructionIndex() {
593           return lastIndex;
594         }
595     
596         void setLastIndex(int lastIndex) {
597           this.lastIndex = lastIndex;
598         }
599     
600         void makeExitBlock() {
601           kind = EXIT;
602         }
603     
604         void makeEntryBlock() {
605           kind = ENTRY;
606         }
607     
608         void makeHandlerBlock() {
609           kind = HANDLER;
610         }
611     
612         @Override
613         public boolean isEntryBlock() {
614           return kind == ENTRY;
615         }
616     
617         @Override
618         public boolean isExitBlock() {
619           return kind == EXIT;
620         }
621     
622         public boolean isHandlerBlock() {
623           return kind == HANDLER;
624         }
625     
626         @Override
627         public String toString() {
628           return "PreBB" + number + ":" + firstIndex + ".." + lastIndex;
629         }
630     
631         private List<SSAInstruction> instructions() {
632           return instructions;
633         }
634     
635         @Override
636         public boolean isCatchBlock() {
637           return (lastIndex > -1) && (instructions.get(0) instanceof SSAGetCaughtExceptionInstruction);
638         }
639     
640         @Override
641         public IMethod getMethod() {
642           return null;
643         }
644     
645         @Override
646         public Iterator<SSAInstruction> iterator() {
647           return instructions.iterator();
648         }
649       }

651       protected final class UnwindState {
652         final CAstNode unwindAst;
653     
654         final WalkContext astContext;
655     
656         final CAstVisitor<WalkContext> astVisitor;
657     
658         UnwindState(CAstNode unwindAst, WalkContext astContext, CAstVisitor<WalkContext> astVisitor) {
659           this.unwindAst = unwindAst;
660           this.astContext = astContext;
661           this.astVisitor = astVisitor;
662         }
663     
664         public UnwindState getParent() {
665           return astContext.getUnwindState();
666         }
667     
668         @Override
669         public int hashCode() {
670           return astContext.hashCode() * unwindAst.hashCode() * astVisitor.hashCode();
671         }
672     
673         @Override
674         public boolean equals(Object o) {
675           if (o instanceof UnwindState) {
676             if (((UnwindState) o).unwindAst != unwindAst)
677               return false;
678             if (((UnwindState) o).astVisitor != astVisitor)
679               return false;
680             if (getParent() == null) {
681               return ((UnwindState) o).getParent() == null;
682             } else {
683               return getParent().equals(((UnwindState) o).getParent());
684             }
685           }
686     
687           return false;
688         }
689     
690         boolean covers(UnwindState other) {
691           if (equals(other))
692             return true;
693           if (getParent() != null)
694             return getParent().covers(other);
695           return false;
696         }
697       }

699       /**
700        * holds the control-flow graph as it is being constructed. When construction
701        * is complete, information is stored in an {@link AstCFG}
702        */
703       @SuppressWarnings("javadoc")
704       public final class IncipientCFG extends SparseNumberedGraph<PreBasicBlock> {
705     
706         protected class Unwind {
707           private final Map<PreBasicBlock, UnwindState> unwindData = new LinkedHashMap<PreBasicBlock, UnwindState>();
708     
709           /**
710            * a cache of generated blocks
711            */
712           private final Map<Pair<UnwindState, Pair<PreBasicBlock, Boolean>>, PreBasicBlock> code = new LinkedHashMap<Pair<UnwindState, Pair<PreBasicBlock, Boolean>>, PreBasicBlock>();
713     
714           void setUnwindState(PreBasicBlock block, UnwindState context) {
715             unwindData.put(block, context);
716           }
717     
718           void setUnwindState(CAstNode node, UnwindState context) {
719             unwindData.put(nodeToBlock.get(node), context);
720           }
721     
722           /**
723            * When adding an edge from source to target, it is possible that certain
724            * exception-handling code needs to be executed before the control is
725            * actually transfered to target. This method determines if this is the
726            * case, and if so, it generates the exception handler blocks and adds an
727            * appropriate edge to the target. It returns the basic block that should
728            * be the target of the edge from source (target itself if there is no
729            * exception-handling code, the initial catch block otherwise)
730            */
731           public PreBasicBlock findOrCreateCode(PreBasicBlock source, PreBasicBlock target, final boolean exception) {
732             UnwindState sourceContext = unwindData.get(source);
733             final CAstNode dummy = exception ? (new CAstImpl()).makeNode(CAstNode.EMPTY) : null;
734     
735             // no unwinding is needed, so jump to target block directly
736             if (sourceContext == null)
737               return target;
738     
739             WalkContext astContext = sourceContext.astContext;
740             UnwindState targetContext = null;
741             if (target != null)
742               targetContext = unwindData.get(target);
743     
744             // in unwind context, but catch in same (or inner) unwind context
745             if (targetContext != null && targetContext.covers(sourceContext))
746               return target;
747     
748             Pair<UnwindState, Pair<PreBasicBlock, Boolean>> key = Pair.make(sourceContext, Pair.make(target, exception));
749     
750             if (code.containsKey(key)) {
751               return code.get(key);
752     
753             } else {
754               int e = -1;
755               PreBasicBlock currentBlock = getCurrentBlock();
756               if (!isDeadBlock(currentBlock)) {
757                 addInstruction(insts.GotoInstruction(currentInstruction, -1));
758                 newBlock(false);
759               }
760               PreBasicBlock startBlock = getCurrentBlock();
761               if (exception) {
762                 setCurrentBlockAsHandler();
763                 e = sourceContext.astContext.currentScope().allocateTempValue();
764                 addInstruction(insts.GetCaughtExceptionInstruction(currentInstruction, startBlock.getNumber(), e));
765                 sourceContext.astContext.setCatchType(startBlock, defaultCatchType());
766               }
767     
768               while (sourceContext != null && (targetContext == null || !targetContext.covers(sourceContext))) {
769                 final CAstRewriter.Rewrite ast = (new CAstCloner(new CAstImpl()) {
770                   @Override
771                   protected CAstNode flowOutTo(Map<Pair<CAstNode, NoKey>, CAstNode> nodeMap, CAstNode oldSource, Object label,
772                       CAstNode oldTarget, CAstControlFlowMap orig, CAstSourcePositionMap src) {
773                     if (exception && !isExceptionLabel(label)) {
774                       return dummy;
775                     } else {
776                       return oldTarget;
777                     }
778                   }
779                 }).copy(sourceContext.unwindAst, sourceContext.astContext.getControlFlow(), sourceContext.astContext.getSourceMap(),
780                     sourceContext.astContext.top().getNodeTypeMap(), sourceContext.astContext.top().getAllScopedEntities());
781                 sourceContext.astVisitor.visit(ast.newRoot(), new DelegatingContext(sourceContext.astContext) {
782                   @Override
783                   public CAstSourcePositionMap getSourceMap() {
784                     return ast.newPos();
785                   }
786     
787                   @Override
788                   public CAstControlFlowMap getControlFlow() {
789                     return ast.newCfg();
790                   }
791                 }, sourceContext.astVisitor);
792     
793                 sourceContext = sourceContext.getParent();
794               }
795     
796               PreBasicBlock endBlock = getCurrentBlock();
797               if (exception) {
798                 addPreNode(dummy);
799                 doThrow(astContext, e);
800               } else {
801                 addInstruction(insts.GotoInstruction(currentInstruction, -1));
802               }
803               newBlock(false);
804     
805               addEdge(currentBlock, getCurrentBlock());
806               if (target != null) {
807                 addEdge(endBlock, target);
808     
809                 // `null' target is idiom for branch/throw to exit
810               } else {
811                 addDelayedEdge(endBlock, exitMarker, exception);
812               }
813     
814               code.put(key, startBlock);
815               return startBlock;
816             }
817           }
818         }
819     
820         private Unwind unwind = null;
821     
822         private final List<PreBasicBlock> blocks = new ArrayList<PreBasicBlock>();
823     
824         private PreBasicBlock entryBlock;
825         
826         private final Map<CAstNode, PreBasicBlock> nodeToBlock = new LinkedHashMap<CAstNode, PreBasicBlock>();
827     
828         private final Map<Object, Set<Pair<PreBasicBlock, Boolean>>> delayedEdges = new LinkedHashMap<Object, Set<Pair<PreBasicBlock, Boolean>>>();
829     
830         private final Object exitMarker = new Object();
831     
832         private final Set<PreBasicBlock> deadBlocks = new LinkedHashSet<PreBasicBlock>();
833     
834         private final Set<PreBasicBlock> normalToExit = new LinkedHashSet<PreBasicBlock>();
835     
836         private final Set<PreBasicBlock> exceptionalToExit = new LinkedHashSet<PreBasicBlock>();
837     
838         private Position[] linePositions = new Position[10];
839     
840         private boolean hasCatchBlock = false;
841     
842         /**
843          * does the method have any monitor operations?
844          */
845         private boolean hasMonitorOp = false;
846     
847         private int currentInstruction = 0;
848     
849         private PreBasicBlock currentBlock;
850     
851         public int getCurrentInstruction() {
852           return currentInstruction;
853         }

855         public PreBasicBlock getCurrentBlock() {
856           return currentBlock;
857         }
858     
859         boolean hasCatchBlock() {
860           return hasCatchBlock;
861         }
862     
863         boolean hasMonitorOp() {
864           return hasMonitorOp;
865         }

867         void noteCatchBlock() {
868           hasCatchBlock = true;
869         }

871         Position[] getLinePositionMap() {
872           return linePositions;

875         /**
876          * create a new basic block, and set it as the current block.
877          * 
878          * @param fallThruFromPrior
879          *          should a fall-through edge be added from the previous block
880          *          (value of currentBlock at entry)? if false, the newly created
881          *          block is marked as a dead block, as it has no incoming edges.
882          * @return the new block
883          */
884         public PreBasicBlock newBlock(boolean fallThruFromPrior) {
885           // optimization: if we have a fall-through from an empty block, just
886           // return the empty block
887           if (fallThruFromPrior && !currentBlock.isEntryBlock() && currentBlock.instructions().size() == 0) {
888             return currentBlock;
889           }
890     
891           PreBasicBlock previous = currentBlock;
892           currentBlock = new PreBasicBlock();
893           addNode(currentBlock);
894           blocks.add(currentBlock);
895     
896           if (DEBUG_CFG)
897             System.err.println(("adding new block (node) " + currentBlock));
898           if (fallThruFromPrior) {
899             if (DEBUG_CFG)
900               System.err.println(("adding fall-thru edge " + previous + " --> " + currentBlock));
901             addEdge(previous, currentBlock);
902           } else {
903             deadBlocks.add(currentBlock);
904           }
905     
906           return currentBlock;
907         }
908     
909         /**
910          * record a delayed edge addition from src to dst. Edge will be added when
911          * appropriate; see {@link #checkForRealizedEdges(CAstNode)} and
912          * {@link #checkForRealizedExitEdges(PreBasicBlock)}
913          */
914         private void addDelayedEdge(PreBasicBlock src, Object dst, boolean exception) {
915           MapUtil.findOrCreateSet(delayedEdges, dst).add(Pair.make(src, exception));
916         }
917     
918         void makeEntryBlock(PreBasicBlock bb) {
919           entryBlock = bb;
920           bb.makeEntryBlock();
921         }
922     
923         void makeExitBlock(PreBasicBlock bb) {
924           bb.makeExitBlock();
925     
926           for (Iterator<? extends PreBasicBlock> ps = getPredNodes(bb); ps.hasNext();)
927             normalToExit.add(ps.next());
928     
929           // now that we have created the exit block, add the delayed edges to the
930           // exit
931           checkForRealizedExitEdges(bb);
932         }
933     
934         void setCurrentBlockAsHandler() {
935           currentBlock.makeHandlerBlock();
936         }
937     
938         boolean hasDelayedEdges(CAstNode n) {
939           return delayedEdges.containsKey(n);
940         }
941     
942         /**
943          * given some n which is now mapped by nodeToBlock, add any delayed edges to
944          * n's block
945          */
946         private void checkForRealizedEdges(CAstNode n) {
947           if (delayedEdges.containsKey(n)) {
948             for (Iterator<Pair<PreBasicBlock, Boolean>> ss = delayedEdges.get(n).iterator(); ss.hasNext();) {
949               Pair<PreBasicBlock, Boolean> s = ss.next();
950               PreBasicBlock src = s.fst;
951               boolean exception = s.snd;
952               if (unwind == null) {
953                 addEdge(src, nodeToBlock.get(n));
954               } else {
955                 PreBasicBlock target = nodeToBlock.get(n);
956                 addEdge(src, unwind.findOrCreateCode(src, target, exception));
957               }
958             }
959     
960             delayedEdges.remove(n);
961           }
962         }
963     
964         /**
965          * add any delayed edges to the exit block
966          */
967         private void checkForRealizedExitEdges(PreBasicBlock exitBlock) {
968           if (delayedEdges.containsKey(exitMarker)) {
969             for (Iterator<Pair<PreBasicBlock, Boolean>> ss = delayedEdges.get(exitMarker).iterator(); ss.hasNext();) {
970               Pair<PreBasicBlock, Boolean> s = ss.next();
971               PreBasicBlock src = s.fst;
972               boolean exception = s.snd;
973               addEdge(src, exitBlock);
974               if (exception)
975                 exceptionalToExit.add(src);
976               else
977                 normalToExit.add(src);
978             }
979     
980             delayedEdges.remove(exitMarker);
981           }
982         }
983     
984         private void setUnwindState(CAstNode node, UnwindState context) {
985           if (unwind == null)
986             unwind = new Unwind();
987           unwind.setUnwindState(node, context);
988         }
989     
990         public void addPreNode(CAstNode n) {
991           addPreNode(n, null);
992         }
993     
994         /**
995          * associate n with the current block, and update the current unwind state
996          */
997         public void addPreNode(CAstNode n, UnwindState context) {
998           if (DEBUG_CFG)
999             System.err.println(("adding pre-node " + n));
1000           nodeToBlock.put(n, currentBlock);
1001           deadBlocks.remove(currentBlock);
1002           if (context != null)
1003             setUnwindState(n, context);
1004           // now that we've associated n with a block, add associated delayed edges
1005           checkForRealizedEdges(n);
1006         }
1007     
1008         public void addPreEdge(CAstNode src, CAstNode dst, boolean exception) {
1009           assert nodeToBlock.containsKey(src);
1010           addPreEdge(nodeToBlock.get(src), dst, exception);
1011         }
1012     
1013         /**
1014          * if dst is associated with a basic block b, add an edge from src to b.
1015          * otherwise, record the edge addition as delayed.
1016          */
1017         public void addPreEdge(PreBasicBlock src, CAstNode dst, boolean exception) {
1018           if (dst == CAstControlFlowMap.EXCEPTION_TO_EXIT) {
1019             assert exception;
1020             addPreEdgeToExit(src, exception);
1021           } else if (nodeToBlock.containsKey(dst)) {
1022             PreBasicBlock target = nodeToBlock.get(dst);
1023             if (DEBUG_CFG)
1024               System.err.println(("adding pre-edge " + src + " --> " + dst));
1025             if (unwind == null) {
1026               addEdge(src, target);
1027             } else {
1028               addEdge(src, unwind.findOrCreateCode(src, target, exception));
1029             }
1030           } else {
1031             if (DEBUG_CFG)
1032               System.err.println(("adding delayed pre-edge " + src + " --> " + dst));
1033             addDelayedEdge(src, dst, exception);
1034           }
1035         }
1036     
1037         public void addPreEdgeToExit(CAstNode src, boolean exception) {
1038           assert nodeToBlock.containsKey(src);
1039           addPreEdgeToExit(nodeToBlock.get(src), exception);
1040         }
1041     
1042         public void addPreEdgeToExit(PreBasicBlock src, boolean exception) {
1043           if (unwind != null) {
1044             PreBasicBlock handlers = unwind.findOrCreateCode(src, null, exception);
1045             if (handlers != null) {
1046               addEdge(src, handlers);
1047               return;
1048             }
1049           }
1050     
1051           addDelayedEdge(src, exitMarker, exception);
1052         }
1053     
1054         @Override
1055         public void addEdge(PreBasicBlock src, PreBasicBlock dst) {
1056           super.addEdge(src, dst);
1057           deadBlocks.remove(dst);
1058         }
1059     
1060         boolean isDeadBlock(PreBasicBlock block) {
1061           return deadBlocks.contains(block);
1062         }
1063     
1064         public PreBasicBlock getBlock(CAstNode n) {
1065           return nodeToBlock.get(n);
1066         }
1067     
1068         /**
1069          * mark the current position as the position for the instruction
1070          */
1071         private void noteLinePosition(int instruction) {
1072           if (linePositions.length < (instruction + 1)) {
1073             Position[] newData = new Position[instruction * 2 + 1];
1074             System.arraycopy(linePositions, 0, newData, 0, linePositions.length);
1075             linePositions = newData;
1076           }
1077     
1078           linePositions[instruction] = getCurrentPosition();
1079         }
1080     
1081         public void addInstruction(SSAInstruction n) {
1082           deadBlocks.remove(currentBlock);
1083     
1084           int inst = currentInstruction++;
1085     
1086           noteLinePosition(inst);
1087     
1088           if (currentBlock.instructions().size() == 0) {
1089             currentBlock.setFirstIndex(inst);
1090           } else {
1091             for(SSAInstruction priorInst : currentBlock.instructions()) {
1092               assert ! (priorInst instanceof SSAGotoInstruction);
1093             }
1094             assert !(n instanceof SSAGetCaughtExceptionInstruction);
1095           }
1096     
1097           if (DEBUG_CFG) {
1098             System.err.println(("adding " + n + " at " + inst + " to " + currentBlock));
1099           }
1100     
1101           if (n instanceof SSAMonitorInstruction) {
1102             hasMonitorOp = true;
1103           }
1104     
1105           currentBlock.instructions().add(n);
1106     
1107           currentBlock.setLastIndex(inst);
1108         }
1109       }
1110     
1111       /**
1112        * data structure for the final CFG for a method, based on the information in
1113        * an {@link IncipientCFG}
1114        */
1115       protected final static class AstCFG extends AbstractCFG<SSAInstruction, PreBasicBlock> {
1116         private final SSAInstruction[] instructions;
1117     
1118         private final int[] instructionToBlockMap;
1119     
1120         private final int[] pcMap;
1121         
1122         private final String functionName;
1123     
1124         private final SymbolTable symtab;
1125     
1126         private interface EdgeOperation {
1127           void act(PreBasicBlock src, PreBasicBlock dst);
1128         }
1129         
1130         private void transferEdges(Set<PreBasicBlock> blocks, 
1131                                           IncipientCFG icfg,
1132                                           EdgeOperation normal,
1133                                           EdgeOperation except) {
1134           for (PreBasicBlock src : blocks) {
1135             for (Iterator j = icfg.getSuccNodes(src); j.hasNext();) {
1136               PreBasicBlock dst = (PreBasicBlock) j.next();
1137               if (isCatchBlock(dst.getNumber()) || (dst.isExitBlock() && icfg.exceptionalToExit.contains(src))) {
1138                 except.act(src, dst);
1139               }
1140     
1141               if (dst.isExitBlock() ? icfg.normalToExit.contains(src) : !isCatchBlock(dst.getNumber())) {
1142                 normal.act(src, dst);
1143               }
1144             }
1145           }
1146         }
1147         
1148         private boolean checkBlockBoundaries(IncipientCFG icfg) {
1149           MutableIntSet boundaries = IntSetUtil.make();
1150           for(PreBasicBlock b : icfg) {
1151             if (b.getFirstInstructionIndex() >= 0) {
1152               if (boundaries.contains(b.getFirstInstructionIndex()))  {
1153                 return false;
1154               }
1155               boundaries.add(b.getFirstInstructionIndex());
1156             }
1157             if (b.getLastInstructionIndex() >= 0 && b.getLastInstructionIndex() != b.getFirstInstructionIndex()) {
1158               if (boundaries.contains(b.getLastInstructionIndex())) {
1159                 return false;            
1160               }
1161               boundaries.add(b.getLastInstructionIndex());
1162             }
1163           }
1164           return true;
1165         }
1166         
1167         AstCFG(CAstEntity n, IncipientCFG icfg, SymbolTable symtab, SSAInstructionFactory insts) {
1168           super(null);
1169           
1170           Set<PreBasicBlock> liveBlocks = DFS.getReachableNodes(icfg, Collections.singleton(icfg.entryBlock));
1171           List<PreBasicBlock> blocks = icfg.blocks;
1172           boolean hasDeadBlocks = blocks.size() > liveBlocks.size();
1173           
1174           assert checkBlockBoundaries(icfg);
1175           
1176           this.symtab = symtab;
1177           functionName = n.getName();
1178           instructionToBlockMap = new int[liveBlocks.size()];
1179           pcMap = hasDeadBlocks? new int[ icfg.currentInstruction ]: null;
1180           
1181           final Map<PreBasicBlock, Collection<PreBasicBlock>> normalEdges = 
1182             hasDeadBlocks? HashMapFactory.<PreBasicBlock,Collection<PreBasicBlock>>make() : null;
1183           final Map<PreBasicBlock, Collection<PreBasicBlock>> exceptionalEdges = 
1184             hasDeadBlocks? HashMapFactory.<PreBasicBlock,Collection<PreBasicBlock>>make() : null;
1185           if (hasDeadBlocks) {
1186             transferEdges(liveBlocks, icfg, new EdgeOperation() {
1187               @Override
1188               public void act(PreBasicBlock src, PreBasicBlock dst) {
1189                 if (! normalEdges.containsKey(src)) {
1190                   normalEdges.put(src, HashSetFactory.<PreBasicBlock>make());
1191                 }
1192                 normalEdges.get(src).add(dst);
1193               }
1194             }, new EdgeOperation() {
1195               @Override
1196               public void act(PreBasicBlock src, PreBasicBlock dst) {
1197                 if (! exceptionalEdges.containsKey(src)) {
1198                   exceptionalEdges.put(src, HashSetFactory.<PreBasicBlock>make());
1199                 }
1200                 exceptionalEdges.get(src).add(dst);
1201               }         
1202             });
1203           }
1204           
1205           int instruction = 0;
1206           for (int i = 0, blockNumber = 0; i < blocks.size(); i++) {
1207             PreBasicBlock block = blocks.get(i);
1208             block.setGraphNodeId(-1);
1209             if (liveBlocks.contains(block)) {
1210               if (hasDeadBlocks) {
1211                 int offset = 0;
1212                 for(int oldPC = block.getFirstInstructionIndex(); 
1213                     offset < block.instructions().size();
1214                     oldPC++, offset++) {
1215                   pcMap[instruction + offset] = oldPC;
1216                 }
1217               }
1218               if (block.getFirstInstructionIndex() >= 0) {
1219                 block.setFirstIndex(instruction);
1220                 block.setLastIndex((instruction += block.instructions().size()) - 1);
1221               }
1222               instructionToBlockMap[blockNumber] = block.getLastInstructionIndex();
1223     
1224               this.addNode(block);
1225               if (block.isCatchBlock()) {
1226                 setCatchBlock(blockNumber);
1227               }
1228     
1229               if (DEBUG_CFG) {
1230                 System.err.println(("added " + blocks.get(i) + " to final CFG as " + getNumber(blocks.get(i))));
1231               } 
1232               
1233               blockNumber++;
1234             }
1235           }
1236           if (DEBUG_CFG)
1237             System.err.println((getMaxNumber() + " blocks total"));
1238     
1239           init();
1240     
1241           if (hasDeadBlocks) {
1242             for (int i = 0; i < blocks.size(); i++) {
1243               PreBasicBlock src = blocks.get(i);
1244               if (liveBlocks.contains(src)) {
1245                 if (normalEdges.containsKey(src)) {
1246                   for(PreBasicBlock succ : normalEdges.get(src)) {
1247                     addNormalEdge(src, succ);
1248                   }
1249                 }
1250                 if (exceptionalEdges.containsKey(src)) {
1251                   for(PreBasicBlock succ : exceptionalEdges.get(src)) {
1252                     addExceptionalEdge(src, succ);
1253                   }
1254                 }
1255               }
1256             }
1257           } else {
1258             transferEdges(liveBlocks, icfg, new EdgeOperation() {
1259               @Override
1260               public void act(PreBasicBlock src, PreBasicBlock dst) {
1261                 addNormalEdge(src, dst);
1262               }
1263             }, new EdgeOperation() {
1264               @Override
1265               public void act(PreBasicBlock src, PreBasicBlock dst) {
1266                 addExceptionalEdge(src, dst);
1267               }
1268             });
1269           }
1270           
1271           int x = 0;
1272           instructions = new SSAInstruction[icfg.currentInstruction];
1273           for (int i = 0; i < blocks.size(); i++) {
1274             if (liveBlocks.contains(blocks.get(i))) {
1275               List<SSAInstruction> bi = blocks.get(i).instructions();
1276               for (int j = 0; j < bi.size(); j++) {
1277                 SSAInstruction inst = bi.get(j);
1278                 if (inst instanceof SSAGetCaughtExceptionInstruction) {
1279                   SSAGetCaughtExceptionInstruction ci = (SSAGetCaughtExceptionInstruction) inst;
1280                   if (ci.getBasicBlockNumber() != blocks.get(i).getNumber()) {
1281                     inst = insts.GetCaughtExceptionInstruction(x, blocks.get(i).getNumber(), ci.getException());
1282                   }
1283                 } else if (inst instanceof SSAGotoInstruction) {
1284                   Iterator<PreBasicBlock> succs = this.getNormalSuccessors(blocks.get(i)).iterator();
1285                   if (succs.hasNext()) {
1286                     PreBasicBlock target = succs.next();
1287                     assert !succs.hasNext() : "unexpected successors for block " + blocks.get(i) + ": " + target + " and " + succs.next();
1288                     inst = insts.GotoInstruction(x, target.firstIndex);
1289                   } else {
1290                     // goto to the end of the method, so the instruction is unnecessary
1291                     inst = null;
1292                   }
1293                 } else if (inst instanceof SSAConditionalBranchInstruction) {
1294                   Iterator<PreBasicBlock> succs = this.getNormalSuccessors(blocks.get(i)).iterator();
1295                   assert succs.hasNext();
1296                   int target;
1297                   int t1 = succs.next().firstIndex;
1298                   if (succs.hasNext()) {
1299                     int t2 = succs.next().firstIndex;
1300                     if (t1 == x+1) {
1301                       target = t2;
1302                     } else {
1303                       target = t1;
1304                     }
1305                   } else {
1306                     target = t1;
1307                   }
1308                   SSAConditionalBranchInstruction branch = (SSAConditionalBranchInstruction) inst;
1309                   inst = insts.ConditionalBranchInstruction(x, branch.getOperator(), branch.getType(), branch.getUse(0), branch.getUse(1), target);
1310                 }
1311                 
1312                 instructions[x++] = inst;
1313               }
1314             }
1315           }
1316         }
1317     
1318         @Override
1319         public int hashCode() {
1320           return functionName.hashCode();
1321         }
1322     
1323         @Override
1324         public boolean equals(Object o) {
1325           return (o instanceof AstCFG) && functionName.equals(((AstCFG) o).functionName);
1326         }
1327     
1328         @Override
1329         public PreBasicBlock getBlockForInstruction(int index) {
1330           for (int i = 1; i < getNumberOfNodes() - 1; i++)
1331             if (index <= instructionToBlockMap[i])
1332               return getNode(i);
1333     
1334           return null;
1335         }
1336     
1337         @Override
1338         public SSAInstruction[] getInstructions() {
1339           return instructions;
1340         }
1341     
1342         @Override
1343         public int getProgramCounter(int index) {
1344           return pcMap == null? index: pcMap[index];
1345         }
1346     
1347         @Override
1348         public String toString() {
1349           SSAInstruction[] insts = getInstructions();
1350           StringBuffer s = new StringBuffer("CAst CFG of " + functionName);
1351           int params[] = symtab.getParameterValueNumbers();
1352           for (int i = 0; i < params.length; i++)
1353             s.append(" ").append(params[i]);
1354           s.append("\n");
1355     
1356           for (int i = 0; i < getNumberOfNodes(); i++) {
1357             PreBasicBlock bb = getNode(i);
1358             s.append(bb).append("\n");
1359     
1360             for (Iterator ss = getSuccNodes(bb); ss.hasNext();)
1361               s.append("    -->" + ss.next() + "\n");
1362     
1363             for (int j = bb.getFirstInstructionIndex(); j <= bb.getLastInstructionIndex(); j++)
1364               if (insts[j] != null)
1365                 s.append("  " + insts[j].toString(symtab) + "\n");
1366           }
1367     
1368           s.append("-- END --");
1369           return s.toString();
1370         }
1371       }

1548       private abstract class AbstractScope implements Scope {
1549         private final Scope parent;
1550     
1551         private final Map<String, Symbol> values = new LinkedHashMap<String, Symbol>();
1552     
1553         private final Map<String, String> caseInsensitiveNames = new LinkedHashMap<String, String>();
1554     
1555         protected abstract SymbolTable getUnderlyingSymtab();
1556     
1557         @Override
1558         public Scope getParent() {
1559           return parent;
1560         }
1561     
1562         @Override
1563         public int size() {
1564           return getUnderlyingSymtab().getMaxValueNumber() + 1;
1565         }
1566     
1567         @Override
1568         public Iterator<String> getAllNames() {
1569           return values.keySet().iterator();
1570         }
1571     
1572         @Override
1573         public int allocateTempValue() {
1574           return getUnderlyingSymtab().newSymbol();
1575         }
1576     
1577         @Override
1578         public int getConstantValue(Object o) {
1579           if (o instanceof Integer) {
1580             return getUnderlyingSymtab().getConstant(((Integer) o).intValue());
1581           } else if (o instanceof Float) {
1582             return getUnderlyingSymtab().getConstant(((Float) o).floatValue());
1583           } else if (o instanceof Double) {
1584             return getUnderlyingSymtab().getConstant(((Double) o).doubleValue());
1585           } else if (o instanceof Long) {
1586             return getUnderlyingSymtab().getConstant(((Long) o).longValue());
1587           } else if (o instanceof String) {
1588             return getUnderlyingSymtab().getConstant((String) o);
1589           } else if (o instanceof Boolean) {
1590             return getUnderlyingSymtab().getConstant((Boolean) o);
1591           } else if (o instanceof Character) {
1592             return getUnderlyingSymtab().getConstant(((Character) o).charValue());
1593           } else if (o instanceof Byte) {
1594             return getUnderlyingSymtab().getConstant(((Byte) o).byteValue());
1595           } else if (o instanceof Short) {
1596             return getUnderlyingSymtab().getConstant(((Short) o).shortValue());
1597           } else if (o == null) {
1598             return getUnderlyingSymtab().getNullConstant();
1599           } else if (o == CAstControlFlowMap.SWITCH_DEFAULT) {
1600             return getUnderlyingSymtab().getConstant("__default label");
1601           } else {
1602             System.err.println(("cannot handle constant " + o));
1603             Assertions.UNREACHABLE();
1604             return -1;
1605           }
1606         }
1607     
1608         @Override
1609         public boolean isConstant(int valueNumber) {
1610           return getUnderlyingSymtab().isConstant(valueNumber);
1611         }
1612     
1613         @Override
1614         public Object getConstantObject(int valueNumber) {
1615           return getUnderlyingSymtab().getConstantValue(valueNumber);
1616         }
1617     
1618         @Override
1619         public void declare(CAstSymbol s, int vn) {
1620           String nm = s.name();
1621           assert !contains(nm) : nm;
1622           if (s.isCaseInsensitive())
1623             caseInsensitiveNames.put(nm.toLowerCase(), nm);
1624           values.put(nm, makeSymbol(s, vn));
1625         }
1626     
1627         @Override
1628         public void declare(CAstSymbol s) {
1629           String nm = s.name();
1630           if (!contains(nm) || lookup(nm).getDefiningScope() != this) {
1631             if (s.isCaseInsensitive())
1632               caseInsensitiveNames.put(nm.toLowerCase(), nm);
1633             values.put(nm, makeSymbol(s));
1634           } else {
1635             assert !s.isFinal() : "trying to redeclare " + nm;
1636           }
1637         }
1638     
1639         AbstractScope(Scope parent) {
1640           this.parent = parent;
1641         }
1642     
1643         private final String mapName(String nm) {
1644           String mappedName = caseInsensitiveNames.get(nm.toLowerCase());
1645           return (mappedName == null) ? nm : mappedName;
1646         }
1647     
1648         protected Symbol makeSymbol(CAstSymbol s) {
1649           return makeSymbol(s.name(), s.type(), s.isFinal(), s.isInternalName(), s.defaultInitValue(), -1, this);
1650         }
1651     
1652         protected Symbol makeSymbol(CAstSymbol s, int vn) {
1653           return makeSymbol(s.name(), s.type(), s.isFinal(), s.isInternalName(), s.defaultInitValue(), vn, this);
1654         }
1655     
1656         abstract protected Symbol makeSymbol(String nm, CAstType type, boolean isFinal, boolean isInternalName, Object defaultInitValue, int vn,
1657             Scope parent);
1658     
1659         @Override
1660         public boolean isCaseInsensitive(String nm) {
1661           return caseInsensitiveNames.containsKey(nm.toLowerCase());
1662         }
1663     
1664         @Override
1665         public Symbol lookup(String nm) {
1666           if (contains(nm)) {
1667             return values.get(mapName(nm));
1668           } else {
1669             Symbol scoped = parent.lookup(nm);
1670             if (scoped != null && getEntityScope() == this && (isGlobal(scoped) || isLexicallyScoped(scoped))) {
1671               values.put(nm,
1672                   makeSymbol(nm, scoped.type(), scoped.isFinal(), scoped.isInternalName(), scoped.defaultInitValue(), -1, scoped.getDefiningScope()));
1673               if (scoped.getDefiningScope().isCaseInsensitive(nm)) {
1674                 caseInsensitiveNames.put(nm.toLowerCase(), nm);
1675               }
1676               return values.get(nm);
1677             } else {
1678               return scoped;
1679             }
1680           }
1681         }
1682     
1683         @Override
1684         public boolean contains(String nm) {
1685           String mappedName = caseInsensitiveNames.get(nm.toLowerCase());
1686           return values.containsKey(mappedName == null ? nm : mappedName);
1687         }
1688     
1689         @Override
1690         public boolean isGlobal(Symbol s) {
1691           return s.getDefiningScope().type() == ScopeType.GLOBAL;
1692         }
1693     
1694         @Override
1695         public abstract boolean isLexicallyScoped(Symbol s);
1696     
1697         protected abstract AbstractScope getEntityScope();
1698     
1699         @Override
1700         public abstract CAstEntity getEntity();
1701       };

1784         return new AbstractScope(parent) {

1788     
1789           @Override

1791             return "scope for " + f.getName();
1792           }

1794           // ctor for scope object
1795           {
1796             for (int i = 0; i < getArgumentCount(f); i++) {

1802                 }

1806                   if (f.getType() instanceof CAstType.Method) {

1808                       return ((CAstType.Method)f.getType()).getDeclaringType();
1809                     } else {
1810                       return (CAstType) ((CAstType.Method)f.getType()).getArgumentTypes().get(yuck-1);
1811                     }
1812                   } else if (f.getType() instanceof CAstType.Function) {
1813                     return (CAstType) ((CAstType.Function)f.getType()).getArgumentTypes().get(yuck);
1814                   } else {
1815                     return topType();

1822                 }

1827                 }

1831                   return false;
1832                 }

1836                   return null;
1837                 }
1838     
1839               });
1840             }

1871           private int find(String n) {
1872             for (int i = 0; i < params.length; i++) {
1873               if (n.equals(params[i])) {
1874                 return i + 1;
1875               }
1876             }
1877     
1878             return -1;
1879           }

1881           @Override
1882           protected Symbol makeSymbol(final String nm, final CAstType type, final boolean isFinal, final boolean isInternalName,
1883               final Object defaultInitValue, final int valueNumber, Scope definer) {
1884             assert nm != null;
1885             assert type != null;
1886             return new AbstractSymbol(definer, isFinal, defaultInitValue) {
1887               final int vn;
1888     
1889               {
1890                 int x = find(nm);
1891                 if (x != -1) {
1892                   assert valueNumber == -1;
1893                   vn = x;
1894                 } else if (valueNumber != -1) {
1895                   vn = valueNumber;
1896                 } else {
1897                   vn = getUnderlyingSymtab().newSymbol();
1898                 }
1899                 if (useDefaultInitValues() && defaultInitValue != null) {
1900                   if (getUnderlyingSymtab().getValue(vn) == null) {
1901                     setDefaultValue(getUnderlyingSymtab(), vn, defaultInitValue);
1902                   }
1903                 }
1904               }

1907               public CAstType type() {
1908                 return type;
1909               }

1911               @Override
1912               public String toString() {
1913                 return nm + ":" + System.identityHashCode(this);
1914               }

1917               public int valueNumber() {
1918                 return vn;
1919               }
1920     
1921               @Override
1922               public boolean isInternalName() {
1923                 return isInternalName;
1924               }
1925     
1926               @Override
1927               public boolean isParameter() {
1928                 return vn <= params.length;
1929               }
1930             };
1931           }

2695       /**
2696        * lexical access information for some entity scope. used during call graph
2697        * construction to handle lexical accesses.
2698        */
2699       public static class AstLexicalInformation implements LexicalInformation {
2700         /**
2701          * the name of this function, as it appears in the definer portion of a
2702          * lexical name
2703          */
2704         private final String functionLexicalName;
2705     
2706         /**
2707          * names possibly accessed in a nested lexical scope, represented as pairs
2708          * (name,nameOfDefiningEntity)
2709          */
2710         private final Pair<String, String>[] exposedNames;
2711     
2712         /**
2713          * map from instruction index and exposed name (via its index in
2714          * {@link #exposedNames}) to the value number for the name at that
2715          * instruction index. This can vary at different instructions due to SSA
2716          * (and this information is updated during {@link SSAConversion}).
2717          */
2718         private final int[][] instructionLexicalUses;
2719     
2720         /**
2721          * maps each exposed name (via its index in {@link #exposedNames}) to its
2722          * value number at method exit.
2723          */
2724         private final int[] exitLexicalUses;
2725     
2726         /**
2727          * the names of the enclosing methods declaring names that are lexically
2728          * accessed by the entity
2729          */
2730         private final String[] scopingParents;
2731     
2732         /**
2733          * all value numbers appearing as entries in {@link #instructionLexicalUses}
2734          * and {@link #exitLexicalUses}, computed lazily
2735          */
2736         private MutableIntSet allExposedUses = null;
2737     
2738         /**
2739          * names of exposed variables of this method that cannot be written outside
2740          */
2741         private final Set<String> readOnlyNames;
2742     
2743         @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
2744         public AstLexicalInformation(AstLexicalInformation original) {
2745           this.functionLexicalName = original.functionLexicalName;
2746     
2747           if (original.exposedNames != null) {
2748             exposedNames = new Pair[original.exposedNames.length];
2749             for (int i = 0; i < exposedNames.length; i++) {
2750               exposedNames[i] = Pair.make(original.exposedNames[i].fst, original.exposedNames[i].snd);
2751             }
2752           } else {
2753             exposedNames = null;
2754           }
2755     
2756           instructionLexicalUses = new int[original.instructionLexicalUses.length][];
2757           for (int i = 0; i < instructionLexicalUses.length; i++) {
2758             int[] x = original.instructionLexicalUses[i];
2759             if (x != null) {
2760               instructionLexicalUses[i] = new int[x.length];
2761               for (int j = 0; j < x.length; j++) {
2762                 instructionLexicalUses[i][j] = x[j];
2763               }
2764             }
2765           }
2766     
2767           if (original.exitLexicalUses != null) {
2768             exitLexicalUses = new int[original.exitLexicalUses.length];
2769             for (int i = 0; i < exitLexicalUses.length; i++) {
2770               exitLexicalUses[i] = original.exitLexicalUses[i];
2771             }
2772           } else {
2773             exitLexicalUses = null;
2774           }
2775     
2776           if (original.scopingParents != null) {
2777             scopingParents = new String[original.scopingParents.length];
2778             for (int i = 0; i < scopingParents.length; i++) {
2779               scopingParents[i] = original.scopingParents[i];
2780             }
2781           } else {
2782             scopingParents = null;
2783           }
2784     
2785           readOnlyNames = original.readOnlyNames;
2786         }
2787     
2788         private int[] buildLexicalUseArray(Pair<Pair<String, String>, Integer>[] exposedNames, String entityName) {
2789           if (exposedNames != null) {
2790             int[] lexicalUses = new int[exposedNames.length];
2791             for (int j = 0; j < exposedNames.length; j++) {
2792               if (entityName == null || entityName.equals(exposedNames[j].fst.snd)) {
2793                 lexicalUses[j] = exposedNames[j].snd;
2794               } else {
2795                 lexicalUses[j] = -1;
2796               }
2797             }
2798     
2799             return lexicalUses;
2800           } else {
2801             return null;
2802           }
2803         }
2804     
2805         private Pair<String, String>[] buildLexicalNamesArray(Pair<Pair<String, String>, Integer>[] exposedNames) {
2806           if (exposedNames != null) {
2807             @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
2808             Pair<String, String>[] lexicalNames = new Pair[exposedNames.length];
2809             for (int j = 0; j < exposedNames.length; j++) {
2810               lexicalNames[j] = exposedNames[j].fst;
2811             }
2812     
2813             return lexicalNames;
2814           } else {
2815             return null;
2816           }
2817         }
2818     
2819         @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
2820         AstLexicalInformation(String entityName, Scope scope, SSAInstruction[] instrs,
2821             Set<Pair<Pair<String, String>, Integer>> exposedNamesForReadSet,
2822             Set<Pair<Pair<String, String>, Integer>> exposedNamesForWriteSet, Set<Access> accesses) {
2823           this.functionLexicalName = entityName;
2824     
2825           Pair<Pair<String, String>, Integer>[] EN = null;
2826           if (exposedNamesForReadSet != null || exposedNamesForWriteSet != null) {
2827             Set<Pair<Pair<String, String>, Integer>> exposedNamesSet = new HashSet<Pair<Pair<String, String>, Integer>>();
2828             if (exposedNamesForReadSet != null) {
2829               exposedNamesSet.addAll(exposedNamesForReadSet);
2830             }
2831             if (exposedNamesForWriteSet != null) {
2832               exposedNamesSet.addAll(exposedNamesForWriteSet);
2833             }
2834             EN = exposedNamesSet.toArray(new Pair[exposedNamesSet.size()]);
2835           }
2836     
2837           if (exposedNamesForReadSet != null) {
2838             Set<String> readOnlyNames = new HashSet<String>();
2839             for (Pair<Pair<String, String>, Integer> v : exposedNamesForReadSet) {
2840               if (entityName != null && entityName.equals(v.fst.snd)) {
2841                 readOnlyNames.add(v.fst.fst);
2842               }
2843             }
2844             if (exposedNamesForWriteSet != null) {
2845               for (Pair<Pair<String, String>, Integer> v : exposedNamesForWriteSet) {
2846                 if (entityName != null && entityName.equals(v.fst.snd)) {
2847                   readOnlyNames.remove(v.fst.fst);
2848                 }
2849               }
2850             }
2851             this.readOnlyNames = readOnlyNames;
2852           } else {
2853             this.readOnlyNames = null;
2854           }
2855     
2856           this.exposedNames = buildLexicalNamesArray(EN);
2857     
2858           // the value numbers stored in exitLexicalUses and instructionLexicalUses
2859           // are identical at first; they will be updated
2860           // as needed during the final SSA conversion
2861           this.exitLexicalUses = buildLexicalUseArray(EN, entityName);
2862     
2863           this.instructionLexicalUses = new int[instrs.length][];
2864           for (int i = 0; i < instrs.length; i++) {
2865             if (instrs[i] instanceof SSAAbstractInvokeInstruction) {
2866               this.instructionLexicalUses[i] = buildLexicalUseArray(EN, null);
2867             }
2868           }
2869     
2870           if (accesses != null) {
2871             Set<String> parents = new LinkedHashSet<String>();
2872             for (Iterator<Access> ACS = accesses.iterator(); ACS.hasNext();) {
2873               Access AC = ACS.next();
2874               if (AC.variableDefiner != null) {
2875                 parents.add(AC.variableDefiner);
2876               }
2877             }
2878             scopingParents = parents.toArray(new String[parents.size()]);
2879     
2880             if (DEBUG_LEXICAL) {
2881               System.err.println(("scoping parents of " + scope.getEntity()));
2882               System.err.println(parents.toString());
2883             }
2884     
2885           } else {
2886             scopingParents = null;
2887           }
2888     
2889           if (DEBUG_NAMES) {
2890             System.err.println(("lexical uses of " + scope.getEntity()));
2891             for (int i = 0; i < instructionLexicalUses.length; i++) {
2892               if (instructionLexicalUses[i] != null) {
2893                 System.err.println(("  lexical uses of " + instrs[i]));
2894                 for (int j = 0; j < instructionLexicalUses[i].length; j++) {
2895                   System.err.println(("    " + this.exposedNames[j].fst + ": " + instructionLexicalUses[i][j]));
2896                 }
2897               }
2898             }
2899           }
2900         }

3102       protected String[] makeNameMap(CAstEntity n, Set<Scope> scopes, SSAInstruction[] insts) {
3103         // all scopes share the same underlying symtab, which is what
3104         // size really refers to.
3105         String[] map = new String[scopes.iterator().next().size() + 1];
3106     
3107         if (DEBUG_NAMES) {
3108           System.err.println(("names array of size " + map.length));
3109         }
3110     
3111         for (Iterator<Scope> S = scopes.iterator(); S.hasNext();) {
3112           Scope scope = S.next();
3113           for (Iterator<String> I = scope.getAllNames(); I.hasNext();) {
3114             String nm = I.next();
3115             
3116             if (ignoreName(nm)) {
3117               continue;
3118             }
3119             
3120             Symbol v = scope.lookup(nm);
3121     
3122             if (v.isInternalName()) {
3123               continue;
3124             }
3125     
3126             // constants can flow to multiple variables
3127             if (scope.isConstant(v.valueNumber()))
3128               continue;
3129     
3130             assert map[v.valueNumber()] == null || map[v.valueNumber()].equals(nm) || ignoreName(map[v.valueNumber()]) : "value number " + v.valueNumber()
3131                 + " mapped to multiple names in " + n.getName() + ": " + nm + " and " + map[v.valueNumber()];
3132     
3133             map[v.valueNumber()] = nm;
3134     
3135             if (DEBUG_NAMES) {
3136               System.err.println(("mapping name " + nm + " to " + v.valueNumber()));
3137             }
3138           }
3139         }
3140     
3141         return map;
3142       }

3271         // entry block
3272         functionContext.cfg().makeEntryBlock(functionContext.cfg().newBlock(false));

3279       public void closeFunctionEntity(final CAstEntity n, WalkContext parentContext, WalkContext functionContext) {
3280         // exit block
3281         functionContext.cfg().makeExitBlock(functionContext.cfg().newBlock(true));
3282     
3283         // create code entry stuff for this entity
3284         SymbolTable symtab = ((AbstractScope) functionContext.currentScope()).getUnderlyingSymtab();
3285         Map<IBasicBlock,TypeReference[]> catchTypes = functionContext.getCatchTypes();
3286         AstCFG cfg = new AstCFG(n, functionContext.cfg(), symtab, insts);
3287         Position[] line = functionContext.cfg().getLinePositionMap();
3288         boolean katch = functionContext.cfg().hasCatchBlock();
3289         boolean monitor = functionContext.cfg().hasMonitorOp();
3290         String[] nms = makeNameMap(n, functionContext.entityScopes(), cfg.getInstructions());
3291     
3292         /*
3293          * Set reachableBlocks = DFS.getReachableNodes(cfg,
3294          * Collections.singleton(cfg.entry()));
3295          * Assertions._assert(reachableBlocks.size() == cfg.getNumberOfNodes(),
3296          * cfg.toString());
3297          */
3298     
3299         // (put here to allow subclasses to handle stuff in scoped entities)
3300         // assemble lexical information
3301         AstLexicalInformation LI = new AstLexicalInformation(functionContext.getEntityName(n), functionContext.currentScope(), cfg.getInstructions(),
3302             functionContext.exposeNameSet(n, false), 
3303             functionContext.exposeNameSet(n, true), 
3304             functionContext.getAccesses(n));
3305     
3306         DebuggingInformation DBG = new AstDebuggingInformation(n.getPosition(), line, nms);
3307     
3308         // actually make code body
3309         defineFunction(n, parentContext, cfg, symtab, katch, catchTypes, monitor, LI, DBG);
3310       }

3416       @Override
3417       protected void leaveFunctionStmt(CAstNode n, WalkContext context, CAstVisitor<WalkContext> visitor) {
3418         int result = processFunctionExpr(n, context);
3419         CAstEntity fn = (CAstEntity) n.getChild(0).getValue();
3420         // FIXME: handle redefinitions of functions
3421         Scope cs = context.currentScope();
3422         if (cs.contains(fn.getName()) && !cs.isLexicallyScoped(cs.lookup(fn.getName())) && !cs.isGlobal(cs.lookup(fn.getName()))) {
3423           // if we already have a local with the function's name, write the function
3424           // value to that local
3425           assignValue(n, context, cs.lookup(fn.getName()), fn.getName(), result);
3426         } else if (topLevelFunctionsInGlobalScope() && context.top().getKind() == CAstEntity.SCRIPT_ENTITY) {
3427           context.getGlobalScope().declare(new FinalCAstSymbol(fn.getName(), fn.getType()));
3428           assignValue(n, context, cs.lookup(fn.getName()), fn.getName(), result);
3429         } else {
3430           context.currentScope().declare(new FinalCAstSymbol(fn.getName(), fn.getType()), result);
3431         }
3432       }

3473       @Override
3474       protected boolean visitLoop(CAstNode n, WalkContext c, CAstVisitor<WalkContext> visitor) {
3475         WalkContext context = c;
3476         // loop test block
3477         context.cfg().newBlock(true);
3478         PreBasicBlock headerB = context.cfg().getCurrentBlock();
3479         visitor.visit(n.getChild(0), context, visitor);
3480     
3481         assert c.getValue(n.getChild(0)) != -1 : "error in loop test " + CAstPrinter.print(n.getChild(0), context.top().getSourceMap())
3482             + " of loop " + CAstPrinter.print(n, context.top().getSourceMap());
3483         context.cfg().addInstruction(
3484             insts.ConditionalBranchInstruction(context.cfg().currentInstruction, translateConditionOpcode(CAstOperator.OP_EQ), null, c.getValue(n.getChild(0)), context
3485                 .currentScope().getConstantValue(new Integer(0)), -1));
3486         PreBasicBlock branchB = context.cfg().getCurrentBlock();
3487     
3488         // loop body
3489         context.cfg().newBlock(true);
3490         visitor.visit(n.getChild(1), context, visitor);
3491         if (!context.cfg().isDeadBlock(context.cfg().getCurrentBlock())) {
3492           context.cfg().addInstruction(insts.GotoInstruction(context.cfg().currentInstruction, -1));
3493           PreBasicBlock bodyB = context.cfg().getCurrentBlock();
3494           context.cfg().addEdge(bodyB, headerB);
3495     
3496           // next block
3497           context.cfg().newBlock(false);
3498         }
3499     
3500         PreBasicBlock nextB = context.cfg().getCurrentBlock();
3501     
3502         // control flow mapping;
3503         context.cfg().addEdge(branchB, nextB);
3504         return true;
3505       }

3615       private boolean handleBinaryOpThrow(CAstNode n, CAstNode op, WalkContext context) {
3616         // currently, only integer / and % throw exceptions
3617         boolean mayBeInteger = false;
3618         Collection labels = context.getControlFlow().getTargetLabels(n);
3619         if (!labels.isEmpty()) {
3620           context.cfg().addPreNode(n, context.getUnwindState());
3621     
3622           mayBeInteger = true;
3623           assert op == CAstOperator.OP_DIV || op == CAstOperator.OP_MOD : CAstPrinter.print(n);
3624           for (Iterator iter = labels.iterator(); iter.hasNext();) {
3625             Object label = iter.next();
3626             CAstNode target = context.getControlFlow().getTarget(n, label);
3627             if (target == CAstControlFlowMap.EXCEPTION_TO_EXIT)
3628               context.cfg().addPreEdgeToExit(n, true);
3629             else
3630               context.cfg().addPreEdge(n, target, true);
3631           }
3632         }
3633     
3634         return mayBeInteger;
3635       }

3637       @Override
3638       protected void leaveBinaryExpr(CAstNode n, WalkContext c, CAstVisitor<WalkContext> visitor) {
3639         WalkContext context = c;
3640         int result = c.getValue(n);
3641         CAstNode l = n.getChild(1);
3642         CAstNode r = n.getChild(2);
3643         assert c.getValue(r) != -1 : CAstPrinter.print(n);
3644         assert c.getValue(l) != -1 : CAstPrinter.print(n);
3645     
3646         boolean mayBeInteger = handleBinaryOpThrow(n, n.getChild(0), context);
3647     
3648         context.cfg().addInstruction(
3649             insts.BinaryOpInstruction(context.cfg().currentInstruction, translateBinaryOpcode(n.getChild(0)), false, false, result, c.getValue(l), c.getValue(r),
3650                 mayBeInteger));
3651     
3652         if (mayBeInteger) {
3653           context.cfg().newBlock(true);
3654         }
3655       }

3710       protected void leaveDeclStmt(CAstNode n, WalkContext c, CAstVisitor<WalkContext> visitor) {

3714         Scope scope = c.currentScope();

3722           } else {

3724             doLocalWrite(c, nm, makeType(t), c.getValue(v));

3726         } else {

3810       protected void processIf(CAstNode n, boolean isExpr, WalkContext c, CAstVisitor<WalkContext> visitor) {
3811         WalkContext context = c;
3812         PreBasicBlock trueB = null, falseB = null;
3813         // conditional
3814         CAstNode l = n.getChild(0);
3815         visitor.visit(l, context, visitor);
3816         context.cfg().addInstruction(
3817             insts.ConditionalBranchInstruction(context.cfg().currentInstruction, translateConditionOpcode(CAstOperator.OP_EQ), null, c.getValue(l), context.currentScope()
3818                 .getConstantValue(new Integer(0)), -1));
3819         PreBasicBlock srcB = context.cfg().getCurrentBlock();
3820         // true clause
3821         context.cfg().newBlock(true);
3822         CAstNode r = n.getChild(1);
3823         visitor.visit(r, context, visitor);
3824         if (isExpr)
3825           context.cfg().addInstruction(new AssignInstruction(context.cfg().currentInstruction, c.getValue(n), c.getValue(r)));
3826         if (n.getChildCount() == 3) {
3827           if (!context.cfg().isDeadBlock(context.cfg().getCurrentBlock())) {
3828             context.cfg().addInstruction(insts.GotoInstruction(context.cfg().currentInstruction, -1));
3829             trueB = context.cfg().getCurrentBlock();
3830     
3831             // false clause
3832             context.cfg().newBlock(false);
3833           }
3834     
3835           falseB = context.cfg().getCurrentBlock();
3836           CAstNode f = n.getChild(2);
3837           visitor.visit(f, context, visitor);
3838           if (isExpr)
3839             context.cfg().addInstruction(new AssignInstruction(context.cfg().currentInstruction, c.getValue(n), c.getValue(f)));
3840         }
3841     
3842         // end
3843         context.cfg().newBlock(true);
3844         if (n.getChildCount() == 3) {
3845           if (trueB != null)
3846             context.cfg().addEdge(trueB, context.cfg().getCurrentBlock());
3847           context.cfg().addEdge(srcB, falseB);
3848         } else {
3849           context.cfg().addEdge(srcB, context.cfg().getCurrentBlock());
3850         }
3851       }

3995       /* Prereq: a.getKind() == ASSIGN_PRE_OP || a.getKind() == ASSIGN_POST_OP */
3996       protected int processAssignOp(CAstNode n, CAstNode v, CAstNode a, int temp, boolean post, WalkContext c) {
3997         WalkContext context = c;
3998         int rval = c.getValue(v);
3999         CAstNode op = a.getChild(2);
4000         int temp2 = context.currentScope().allocateTempValue();
4001     
4002         boolean mayBeInteger = handleBinaryOpThrow(a, op, context);
4003     
4004         context.cfg().addInstruction(
4005             insts.BinaryOpInstruction(context.cfg().currentInstruction, translateBinaryOpcode(op), false, false, temp2, temp, rval, mayBeInteger));
4006     
4007         if (mayBeInteger) {
4008           context.cfg().newBlock(true);
4009         }
4010     
4011         return temp2;
4012       }

4099       /**
4100        * assign rval to nm as appropriate, depending on the scope of ls
4101        */
4102       protected void assignValue(CAstNode n, WalkContext context, Symbol ls, String nm, int rval) {
4103         if (context.currentScope().isGlobal(ls))
4104           doGlobalWrite(context, nm, makeType(ls.type()), rval);
4105         else if (context.currentScope().isLexicallyScoped(ls)) {
4106           doLexicallyScopedWrite(context, nm, makeType(ls.type()), rval);
4107         } else {
4108           assert rval != -1 : CAstPrinter.print(n, context.top().getSourceMap());
4109           doLocalWrite(context, nm, makeType(ls.type()), rval);
4110         }
4111       }

4128       @Override
4129       protected void leaveVarAssignOp(CAstNode n, CAstNode v, CAstNode a, boolean pre, WalkContext c, CAstVisitor<WalkContext> visitor) {
4130         WalkContext context = c;
4131         String nm = (String) n.getChild(0).getValue();
4132         Symbol ls = context.currentScope().lookup(nm);
4133         TypeReference type = makeType(ls.type());
4134         int temp;
4135     
4136         if (context.currentScope().isGlobal(ls))
4137           temp = doGlobalRead(n, context, nm, type);
4138         else if (context.currentScope().isLexicallyScoped(ls)) {
4139           temp = doLexicallyScopedRead(n, context, nm, type);
4140         } else {
4141           temp = doLocalRead(context, nm, type);
4142         }
4143     
4144         if (!pre) {
4145           int ret = context.currentScope().allocateTempValue();
4146           context.cfg().addInstruction(new AssignInstruction(context.cfg().currentInstruction, ret, temp));
4147           c.setValue(n, ret);
4148         }
4149     
4150         int rval = processAssignOp(n, v, a, temp, !pre, c);
4151     
4152         if (pre) {
4153           c.setValue(n, rval);
4154         }
4155     
4156         if (context.currentScope().isGlobal(ls)) {
4157           doGlobalWrite(context, nm, type, rval);
4158         } else if (context.currentScope().isLexicallyScoped(ls)) {
4159           doLexicallyScopedWrite(context, nm, type, rval);
4160         } else {
4161           doLocalWrite(context, nm, type, rval);
4162         }
4163       }
